  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Create Category Schema&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Pre-conditions&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The administrator is logged in to RAM&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Objectives&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    RAM provides a mechanism for creating and editing category schemas. These schemas provide values to categorize assets&#xD;
    when they are submitted.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp; &lt;img height=&quot;302&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/categoryschema.gif&quot; width=&quot;413&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Steps for Web UI&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Go to Administration &amp;gt; Repository Administration &amp;gt; Asset Configuration&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Expand the &lt;strong>Category schemas&lt;/strong> drop down button&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click on the &lt;strong>Create new category schema&lt;/strong> button&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Enter the name and description of the category schema&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add one or more fields, enter the name, the description and if the children are exclusive&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Post-conditions&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The appropriate stakeholders have agreed on the classification schema&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The schema is registered with RAM&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>More Information&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Please see the Rational Asset Manager related sections on developerWorks.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
